191
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,560
Well, you literally create a plan.
嗯，你字面上制定一个计划。

192
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:06,280
You draw a map of what you're going to do.
你画一张你要做什么的路线图。

193
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:08,480
So here, is it only for like travel or?
所以这里，它只用于旅行之类的吗？

194
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,480
No, no, no.
不，不，不。

195
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:13,800
It's like, for example, if we're starting a new project in the company, you can map
比如，如果我们在公司启动一个新项目，你可以规划

196
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:17,200
out the project, what you're going to do this month, next month.
这个项目，这个月、下个月要做什么。

197
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,240
So it's a plan.
所以它是一个计划。

198
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:21,200
So you draw every step in the plan.
所以你画出计划中的每一步。

199
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,440
Every step, right.
每一步，对。

200
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:27,000
So you said, well, I've mapped out this plan for a new project.
所以你说，嗯，我为新项目规划好了这个计划。

201
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,280
Okay, interesting word.
好的，一个有趣的词。

202
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:33,040
I think we should hear some examples of how it's used.
我觉得我们应该听一些它用法的例子。

203
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,960
Example one.
例子一。

204
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,760
So I have the future all mapped out.
所以我已经把未来都规划好了。

205
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:40,680
Well, you'll get a job as a waiter, then we'll get married.
嗯，你会先当个服务员，然后我们结婚。

206
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:45,640
And two years later, we'll start having kids.
两年后，我们开始要孩子。

207
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:48,440
Example two.
例子二。

208
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:54,480
We're mapping out the marketing plan at the meeting today.
我们今天在会议上规划营销方案。

209
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,040
Example three.
例子三。

210
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:04,160
Okay, I've mapped out our trip and it should take about 10 hours.
好的，我已经规划好了我们的行程，大概需要10个小时。

211
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:06,160
All right, so mapped out.
好了，所以“mapped out”这个词。

212
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,160
Really, really clear now.
现在非常清楚了。

213
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,520
Let's take a look at our next word.
我们来看看下一个词。

214
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:14,160
All right, so if you've mapped out a plan, you don't want to screw it up.
好的，如果你已经规划好了一个计划，你就不想搞砸它。

215
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,280
Right, screw it up.
对，“screw it up”。

216
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,480
Screw it up.
搞砸它。

217
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,760
Or screw up.
或者“screw up”。

218
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:19,760
Yep.
是的。

219
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:22,760
So to screw something up means that you made a mistake on something.
所以“screw something up”意思是你在某件事上犯了错。

220
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,760
Or you did something wrong.
或者你做错了什么。

221
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,760
You did it wrong.
你做错了。

222
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:25,760
Yep.
是的。

223
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:31,520
Okay, so for example, if I'm taking an exam and I make a mistake, I screwed up on the
好的，比如，如果我参加考试犯了错，我就在考试中搞砸了。

224
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,520
exam.
考试。

225
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,520
Exactly.
没错。

226
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:37,960
Or for example, here, when we're recording, Marco and I make mistakes a lot.
或者比如，在这里录音时，马可和我经常犯错。

227
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,160
Maybe more me than Marco.
可能我比马可犯得更多。

228
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:40,960
We always screw up.
我们总是搞砸。

229
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,960
Yeah.
是啊。

230
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:42,960
Exactly.
没错。

231
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:45,720
So to make a mistake, it's a really informal word, but very, very common.
所以“犯错”这个词很口语化，但非常非常常用。

232
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,720
Yeah.
是啊。

233
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,760
And you know, it sounds really, really natural when people use this.
你知道，当人们用这个词时，听起来非常自然。

234
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:53,200
All right, so now let's take a look at our last word.
好了，现在我们来看看最后一个词。

235
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,120
Lose your cool.
失去冷静。

236
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,520
Lose your cool.
失去冷静。

237
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,240
Don't lose your cool.
别失去冷静。

238
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,760
So what is this, to lose your cool?
那么“失去冷静”是什么意思？

239
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:00,760
It's a weird expression.
这是个奇怪的表达。

240
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,360
It's a weird expression.
这是个奇怪的表达。

241
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:07,280
Why don't we just give you an example of a person that loses his or her cool.
不如我们直接给你举个例子，看看一个人失去冷静的样子。

242
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:11,640
What do you mean you're not ready to go?
你什么意思，你还没准备好出发？

243
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:12,640
It's time to go.
该走了。

244
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,640
We have to go now.
我们现在就得走。

245
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,640
Boninato!
博尼纳托！

246
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,640
We were supposed to leave!
我们本来应该出发了！

247
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,640
Punietta, now we're sitting here again.
普尼埃塔，现在我们又坐在这儿了。

248
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,640
I'm going to wait for you.
我要等你。

249
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,640
Boninam!
博尼纳姆！

250
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:23,160
Okay, so basically, you lose your temper.
好的，基本上就是，你发脾气了。

251
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,920
You become irritated.
你变得烦躁。

252
